	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Tammuz 21st 5603</date></p>
				<p>To <addressee>Abram Hart Esqr.</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The vestry &#38; members of the</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Congregation &#8220;Mikveh Israel&#8221; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><sic>Bretheren</sic>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">In behalf of the Congrega&#45;<lb/>tion Beth Elohim of this city&#44; we earnestly appeal to you to<lb/> permit your Hazan the <persName>Revd Isaac Leeser</persName> to come on to<lb/> <placeName>Charleston</placeName>&#44; for the purpose of giving Testimony in a case about<lb/> to be tried&#44; which involves questions not only of the<lb/> greatest importance to us&#44; but of deep interest to the<lb/> whole House of <placeName>Israel</placeName>. A party in our Congregation<lb/> have undertaken to sap the foundations of our sacred<lb/> Institutions&#44; and to introduce innovations&#44; which must<lb/> lead to the eventual overthrow of the Jewish Ritual as<lb/> established for age past. With this party unfortunately<lb/> has united our late Hazan the <persName>Revd. G. Poznanski</persName>&#44; and<lb/> we are led to believe that he will be brought forward<lb/> as a witness to maintain these innovations and to endeavor<lb/> to prove them consistent with the Institutions of our<lb/> People. It will need therefore the learning and character<lb/> of some of our best&#45;informed teachers to expose the errors<lb/> and inconsistencies of such innovations&#44; and we know<lb/> no one whose learning and reputation could be more<lb/> certainly relied upon&#44; than the Revd Hazan whom it is<lb/> your good fortune to have. We are struggling to maintain<lb/>  the Institutions and Faith of our common ancestors against<lb/> an array of influence&#44; which but for our Trust in that<lb/> Great Being who will always support the right might<lb/> deter us from our duty. But we are determined to stand<lb/> up to the last&#44; and not permit Rationalism or Infidelity<lb/> to invade our Sanctuary. Fully confident that your<lb/> sympathies are with us&#44; and that you will regard<lb/> us but as the outposts in fighting the Common Battle<lb/> of the Struse<add>&#63;</add> of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; and cannot doubt&#44; that you<lb/> will consent  to spare us your Hazan for a short time.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>The case in which we need the Testimony of your Hazan<lb/> is in such a form that our Lawyers advise us&#44; will need his<lb/> personal presence&#44; as no Testimony can be taken in writing.<lb/> The trial is expected to take place on the <date>8th of August</date><lb/> and we only ask therefore&#44; that you dispense with <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName><lb/> for the space of a Fortnight&#44; after which time we hope he<lb/> will return to you improved in health as our City is perfectly<lb/> healthy.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">With sincere prayers for the prosperity of your<lb/> Congregation. We remain your friends and<lb/> Brethren in <placeName>Israel</placeName> &#45;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Baich<add>&#63;</add> Moses</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sol Moses</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Isaac Woolf</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Abraham Johas<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Attested</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName>S Valentine</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Secry &#38; Treasr.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">K. K. B. E.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways to the right of the list of signatures">Trustees of K. K. B. E.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr. Abraham Hart</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">President of the Congregation &#8220;Mikveh Israel&#8222;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
